<title>Isabel</title>
  <para>written by Rosanna Yuen</para>
  <bridgehead>Setup</bridgehead>

  <informaltable>
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <tbody>
	<row>
	  <entry>Type of Deck</entry>
	  <entry>Standard Deck</entry>
	</row>
	<row>
	  <entry>Tableau</entry>
	  <entry>
	    Thirteen piles.  Deal three cards face down and one card
	    face up on every pile.
	  </entry>
	</row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <bridgehead>Goal</bridgehead>
  <para>
    Remove all cards.
  </para>
  <bridgehead>Rules</bridgehead>
  <para>
    Remove cards in pairs of equal rank.  Every time a card is removed,
    the card underneath is flipped face up and becomes playable.  Empty
    slots are not filled.
  </para>
  <bridgehead>Options</bridgehead>
  <para>None</para>
  <bridgehead>Scoring</bridgehead>
  <para>
    Each pair of cards removed scores two points.
  </para>
  <para>
    Maximum possible score:  52
  </para>
  <bridgehead>Strategy</bridgehead>
  <para>
    Each pile starts with four cards.  The trick is to remember how many
    cards each slot has left at any given time so that you can try to
    remove cards evenly.
  </para>
</chapter>
